RICH A. PAULOO

richpauloo.github.io | richpauloo | rpauloo@ucdavis.edu

Hydrologic Sciences PhD (March 2020) with demonstrated ability to work in interdisciplinary teams on projects bridging hydrology, climate science, underrepresented communities, and public policy. Highly adept in end-to-end analysis of data in any format, with success in two data science competitions hosted by NASA and the West Big Data Hub. Possess 3+ years of experience in scripting non-routine, quantitative analysis of spatial, tabular, natural language, and timeseries data. Highly curious and creative thinker skilled in research design, from data gathering and processing, to statistics, machine learning, data visualization, communication, and drawing policy implications from research. Possess strong interpersonal, presentation, writing, and oratory skills. Able to grasp new concepts and ideas quickly. Motivated by learning new skills and making a difference in the world through scientifically-informed policy.

DATA ANALYSIS EXPERIENCE

  • Winner, California Water Data Challenge ($1,500 Prize) [VIEW PROJECT]
    • Built spatial, statistical, and machine learning models to predict domestic well failure in California during the 2012-2016 drought and future drought scenarios, assessed the vulnerability of low-income communities in California to drought, and developed policy recommendations for meeting these challenges.
  • Runner-Up, NASA Data Visualization Competition ($1,400 Prize) [VIEW SLIDES]
    • Artistic and concise communication and visualization of big geospatial timeseries data.
  • Data Engineer & Developer for UC Water
    • Spatial Database Query Tool for California Well Completion Reports: Spatial database that takes a user defined shapefile and returns the subset of points within that shapefile.
    • Real Time Aquifer Monitoring: End-to-end data extraction-transformation-visualization pipeline scraping monitoring well data sent via telemetry. Includes automated report generation and distribution.
  • Developer Hobbyist
    • Groundwater Quality Data Explorer: Interactive map of multiple groundwater quality databases.
    • Abstr: Interactively swipe through 20,000+ scientific abstracts from the 2017 American Geophysical Union Fall Meeting.
    • Word Cloud Generator: Enter a .txt file and this app returns a word cloud of the most frequently-used non-stop-words.
  • Data Science Blogger (> 1.2k monthly users) [VIEW BLOG]
    • Topics range from statistics in R, to predicting fatal landslides worldwide with machine learning, to data science software installation guides
